<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:22PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Wilkinson, northeastern Bibb, north central Twiggs and southeastern
Jones Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 422 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Mountain Springs, or 11
miles southeast of Gray, moving northwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Macon, Gray, Gordon, Ivey, Postell, James, Mountain Springs,
Griswoldville and Greenberry Crossroads.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
